  "prompt": "Which is best mobile under 15000?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, several smartphones are considered the best options under \u20b915,000 in India. Here are a few noteworthy models you can consider:\n\n1. **Realme Narzo 50**:\n   - **Processor**: MediaTek Helio G96\n   - **Display**: 6.6 inches, 90Hz\n   - **Camera**: Triple rear camera setup (50MP main)\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh with 33W fast charging\n\n2. **Xiaomi Redmi Note 11**:\n   - **Processor**: Qualcomm Snapdragon 680\n   - **Display**: 6.43 inches, Super AMOLED, 90Hz\n   - **Camera**: Quad rear camera (50MP main)\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh with 33W fast charging\n\n3. **Samsung Galaxy M32**:\n   - **Processor**: MediaTek Helio G80\n   - **Display**: 6.4 inches, Super AMOLED, 90Hz\n   - **Camera**: Quad rear camera setup (64MP main)\n   - **Battery**: 6000mAh\n\n4. **Poco M4 Pro**:\n   - **Processor**: MediaTek Dimensity 810\n   - **Display**: 6.67 inches, AMOLED\n   - **Camera**: Triple rear camera (50MP main)\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh with 33W fast charging\n\n5. **Motorola Moto G31**:\n   - **Processor**: MediaTek Helio G85\n   - **Display**: 6.4 inches, AMOLED\n   - **Camera**: Triple rear camera (50MP main)\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh\n\nWhen choosing a smartphone, consider factors such as the processor, camera quality, battery life, and additional features like fast charging and display type. Prices and availability can vary, so it is advisable to check the latest reviews and current prices before making a decision.",
